  "text": ", p15 INK4b ), and lower levels of the apoptotic activators NAIP, BCL-xL, BAX and IRF1, indicating uncontrolled cell cycle progression and resistance to apoptosis. In addition, 5-fluorouracil treatment prompted the CD44 negative cells to proceed to G2 contrary to the G1 cell cycle arrest seen in CD44 positive cells. A further property of cancer-initiating cells is the ability to evade host immunity during tumor establishment. CD44 negative neuroblastoma cells demonstrated such a profile by expressing reduced levels of the chemo-attractant CCL2 and the TNF receptor FAS [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
